alse},{\"answerText\":\"False\",\"isCorrect\":true}]},{\"questionText\":\" Organizations are looking for a robust GRC program that will enable them to manage \\r\\n compliance with regulations and internal policies.\",\"answerOptions\":[{\"answerText\":\"True\",\"isCorrect\":true},{\"answerText\":\"False\",\"isCorrect\":false}]},{\"questionText\":\"Businesses that are running fast and successfully have been able to do so because they\\u2019ve \\r\\n taken the time to develop a flexible and comprehensive GRC ______.\",\"answerOptions\":[{\"answerText\":\"System\",\"isCorrect\":false},{\"answerText\":\"Procedure\",\"isCorrect\":false},{\"answerText\":\"Framework\",\"isCorrect\":true},{\"answerText\":\"None of the above\",\"isCorrect\":false}]},{\"questionText\":\" As organizations are increasingly looking to implement GRC strategies to drive we \\r\\n also understand that getting started with GRC can be challenging.\",\"answerOptions\":[{\"answerText\":\"accountability\",\"isCorrect\":false},{\"answerText\":\"security, efficiency,\",\"isCorrect\":false},{\"answerText\":\"and visibility across the organization,\",\"isCorrect\":false},{\"answerText\":\"All of the above\",\"isCorrect\":true}]}]', NULL, NULL),
(60, 'Quiz', 56, 'TMC', '[{\"questionText\":\"Risk is defined in financial terms as the chance that an outcome or investment\'s actual gains \\r\\n will differ from an expected outcome or return.\",\"answerOptions\":[{\"answerText\":\"True\",\"isCorrect\":true},{\"answerText\":\"False\",\"isCorrect\":false}]},{\"questionText\":\"A ______ is a specific type of compliance risk that occurs when a company fails to follow a \\r\\n government\'s rules for companies.\",\"answerOptions\":[{\"answerText\":\"Strategic risk\",\"isCorrect\":false},{\"answerText\":\"Compliance risk\",\"isCorrect\":false},{\"answerText\":\"Reputational risk\",\"isCorrect\":false},{\"answerText\":\"Legal risk\",\"isCorrect\":true}]},{\"questionText\":\"_______ in business can arise from employees\' failure to perform their essential duties in \\r\\n the workplace.\",\"answerOptions\":[{\"answerText\":\"Competition risk\",\"isCorrect\":false},{\"answerText\":\"Security risk\",\"isCorrect\":true},{\"answerText\":\"Human risk\",\"isCorrect\":false},{\"answerText\":\"Physical risk\",\"isCorrect\":false}]},{\"questionText\":\" Corporate governance is the elaborate set of code prescribed to shape the company \\r\\n management only internally.\",\"answerOptions\":[{\"answerText\":\"True\",\"isCorrect\":false},{\"answerText\":\"False\",\"isCorrect\":true}]},{\"questionText\":\"Internal audit can give additional value by including reviews of the organisation\'s processes \\r\\n and procedures in areas such as:\",\"answerOptions\":[{\"answerText\":\"Corporate culture\",\"isCorrect\":false},{\"answerText\":\"How the organisation first identifies and then chooses how to manage risks\",\"isCorrect\":false},{\"answerText\":\"Sustainability\",\"isCorrect\":false},{\"answerText\":\"All of the above\",\"isCorrect\":true}]},{\"questionText\":\"There are ___ steps in risk management process.\",\"answerOptions\":[{\"answerText\":\"Five\",\"isCorrect\":false},{\"answerText\":\"Three\",\"isCorrect\":false},{\"answerText\":\"Six\",\"isCorrect\":false},{\"answerText\":\"Four\",\"isCorrect\":true}]},{\"questionText\":\"ERM requires the whole organisation to identify, communicate and proactively manage risk, \\r\\n regardless of position or perspective.\",\"answerOptions\":[{\"answerText\":\"True\",\"isCorrect\":true},{\"answerText\":\"False\",\"isCorrect\":false}]},{\"questionText\":\" COSO stands for:\",\"answerOptions\":[{\"answerText\":\"Committee of Sponsoring Organisations of the Treadway Commission\",\"isCorrect\":true},{\"answerText\":\"Community of security organization\",\"isCorrect\":false},{\"answerText\":\"Counsel of Scientific organization\",\"isCorrect\":false},{\"answerText\":\"None of the above \",\"isCorrect\":false}]},{\"questionText\":\" A is an independent assessment of an entity\'s operations to determine \\r\\n if specific programs or functions are working as intended to achieve stated goals.\",\"answerOptions\":[{\"answerText\":\"Operational audit\",\"isCorrect\":false},{\"answerText\":\"Performance audit\",\"isCorrect\":true},{\"answerText\":\"Financial audit\",\"isCorrect\":false},{\"answerText\":\"Contracts audit\",\"isCorrect\":false}]},{\"questionText\":\" Detective controls are designed to find errors or fraud in transactions after they have \\r\\n occurred, as well as identify missing assets or invalid transactions.\",\"answerOptions\":[{\"answerText\":\"True\",\"isCorrect\":true},{\"answerText\":\"False\",\"isCorrect\":false}]}]', NULL, NULL),
(61, 'Quiz', 69, 'TMC', '[{\"questionText\":\" Cyber security is the practice of defending computers, servers, mobile devices, electronic \\r\\n systems, networks, and data from malicious attacks.\",\"answerOptions\":[{\"answerText\":\"True\",\"isCorrect\":true},{\"answerText\":\"False\",\"isCorrect\":false}]},{\"questionText\":\" The purpose of cyber-security is to prevent data breaches, identity theft and cyber-attacks \\r\\n as well as risk management in some cases.\",\"answerOptions\":[{\"answerText\":\"True\",\"isCorrect\":true},{\"answerText\":\"False\",\"isCorrect\":false}]},{\"questionText\":\" A successful cyber-attack cannot cause major damage to your business.\",\"answerOptions\":[{\"answerText\":\"True\",\"isCorrect\":false},{\"answerText\":\"False\",\"isCorrect\":true}]},{\"questionText\":\"Cyber-attacks often result in a substantial financial loss arising from:\",\"answerOptions\":[{\"answerText\":\"theft of corporate information\",\"isCorrect\":false},{\"answerText\":\"theft of financial information (e.g. bank details or payment card details)\",\"isCorrect\":false},{\"answerText\":\"theft of money\",\"isCorrect\":false},{\"answerText\":\"All of the above\",\"isCorrect\":true}]},{\"questionText\":\"Cyber-attacks can damage your business\' reputation and erode the trust your customers \\r\\n have for you. This, in turn, could potentially lead to:\",\"answerOptions\":[{\"answerText\":\"loss of customers\",\"isCorrect\":false},{\"answerText\":\"loss of sales\",\"isCorrect\":false},{\"answerText\":\"reduction in profits\",\"isCorrect\":false},{\"answerText\":\"All of the above\",\"isCorrect\":true}]},{\"questionText\":\" _____ is a malware designed to deny a user or organisation access to files on their \\r\\n computer.\",\"answerOptions\":[{\"answerText\":\"Phishing\",\"isCorrect\":false},{\"answerText\":\"Hacking\",\"isCorrect\":false},{\"answerText\":\"Ransomware\",\"isCorrect\":true},{\"answerText\":\"None of the above\",\"isCorrect\":false}]},{\"questionText\":\"Phishing attacks are social engineering attacks, and they can have a great range of targets \\r\\n depending on the attacker.\",\"answerOptions\":[{\"answerText\":\"True\",\"isCorrect\":true},{\"answerText\":\"False\",\"isCorrect\":false}]},{\"questionText\":\"Whaling is an even more targeted type of phishing that goes after the whales \\u2013 a marine \\r\\n animal even bigger than a fish.\",\"answerOptions\":[{\"answerText\":\"True\",\"isCorrect\":true},{\"answerText\":\"False\",\"isCorrect\":false}]},{\"questionText\":\"____ is the unauthorized transmission of data from within an organisation to an external \\r\\n destination or recipient.\",\"answerOptions\":[{\"answerText\":\"Phishing\",\"isCorrect\":false},{\"answerText\":\"Data leakage\",\"isCorrect\":true},{\"answerText\":\"Ransomware\",\"isCorrect\":false},{\"answerText\":\"None of the above\",\"isCorrect\":false}]},{\"questionText\":\"Hacking refers to activities that seek to compromise digital devices, such as computers, \\r\\n smartphones, tablets, and even entire networks.\",\"answerOptions\":[{\"answerText\":\"True\",\"isCorrect\":true},{\"answerText\":\"False\",\"isCorrect\":false}]}]', NULL, NULL),
(62, 'Quiz', 67, 'TMC', '[{\"questionText\":\" In its most basic form, an AML compliance program includes three fundamental functions:\",\"answerOptions\":[{\"answerText\":\"Assess the risk of new and current customers\",\"isCorrect\":false},{\"answerText\":\" Implement screening measures to weed out clients who present a high risk for financial \\r\\n crimes\",\"isCorrect\":false},{\"answerText\":\"Conduct ongoing monitoring of customer activity\",\"isCorrect\":false},{\"answerText\":\"All of the above\",\"isCorrect\":true}]},{\"questionText\":\" The fight against money laundering is a huge challenge for financial institutions around the \\r\\n world, and as criminal methodologies grow more sophisticated, so must the AML measures \\r\\n put in place to stop them.\",\"answerOptions\":[{\"answerText\":\"True\",\"isCorrect\":true},{\"answerText\":\"False\",\"isCorrect\":false}]},{\"questionText\":\"AI, deployed as part of a firm\\u2019s AML compliance program, represents a series of algorithms \\r\\n that control the digital measures put in place to detect money laundering (and other \\r\\n criminal activities).\",\"answerOptions\":[{\"answerText\":\"True\",\"isCorrect\":true},{\"answerText\":\"False\",\"isCorrect\":false}]},{\"questionText\":\"Human trafficking is not a global issue and can be ignored.\",\"answerOptions\":[{\"answerText\":\"True\",\"isCorrect\":false},{\"answerText\":\"False\",\"isCorrect\":true}]},{\"questionText\":\"The idea of converging cyber _____, AML, and fraud prevention activities to eliminate gaps \\r\\n in financial crime risk management has been discussed for years.\",\"answerOptions\":[{\"answerText\":\"Security\",\"isCorrect\":false},{\"answerText\":\"Intelligence\",\"isCorrect\":true},{\"answerText\":\"Monitoring\",\"isCorrect\":false},{\"answerText\":\"None of the above\",\"isCorrect\":false}]},{\"questionText\":\"One of the most important tools to invest in is antivirus software.\",\"answerOptions\":[{\"answerText\":\"True\",\"isCorrect\":true},{\"answerText\":\"False\",\"isCorrect\":false}]},{\"questionText\":\"By thinking the way a cyber criminal would, security experts can scan their IT environments \\r\\n for vulnerabilities, such as unpatched software, authentication errors, and more. This can be \\r\\n defined as?\",\"answerOptions\":[{\"answerText\":\"Automated monitoring systems\",\"isCorrect\":false},{\"answerText\":\"User behaviour analytics\",\"isCorrect\":false},{\"answerText\":\"Penetration testing\",\"isCorrect\":true},{\"answerText\":\"None of the above\",\"isCorrect\":false}]},{\"questionText\":\"CSPs often provide a number of application programming interfaces (APIs) and interfaces for \\r\\n their customers.\",\"answerOptions\":[{\"answerText\":\"True\",\"isCorrect\":true},{\"answerText\":\"False\",\"isCorrect\":false}]},{\"questionText\":\"Insider threats are a major security issue for any organisation.\",\"answerOptions\":[{\"answerText\":\"True\",\"isCorrect\":true},{\"answerText\":\"False\",\"isCorrect\":false}]},{\"questionText\":\"is a type of social engineering attack often used to steal user data, \\r\\n including login credentials and credit card numbers.\",\"answerOptions\":[{\"answerText\":\"CLOUD ATTACKS\",\"isCorrect\":false},{\"answerText\":\"IOT ATTACKS\",\"isCorrect\":false},{\"answerText\":\"RANSOMWARE ATTACKS\",\"isCorrect\":false},{\"answerText\":\"PHISHING\",\"isCorrect\":true}]}]', NULL, NULL),
(63, 'Quiz', 68, 'TMC', '[{\"questionText\":\"Simply put, strategic risks are risks that a company takes that could potentially result in a major loss.\",\"answerOptions\":[{\"answerText\":\"True\",\"isCorrect\":true},{\"answerText\":\"False\",\"isCorrect\":false}]},{\"questionText\":\" Strategic risk management is the process of identifying, quantifying, and mitigating any risk \\r\\n that affects or is inherent in a company\\u2019s business strategy, strategic objectives, and strategy \\r\\n execution.\",\"answerOptions\":[{\"answerText\":\"True\",\"isCorrect\":true},{\"answerText\":\"False\",\"isCorrect\":false}]},{\"questionText\":\"Strategic risk may include: \",\"answerOptions\":[{\"answerText\":\"Shifts in consumer demand and preferences\",\"isCorrect\":false},{\"answerText\":\"Legal and regulatory change\",\"isCorrect\":false},{\"answerText\":\"Competitive pressure\",\"isCorrect\":false},{\"answerText\":\"All of the above\",\"isCorrect\":true}]},{\"questionText\":\"Strategic risk is a ___ curve.\",\"answerOptions\":[{\"answerText\":\"Flat\",\"isCorrect\":false},{\"answerText\":\"Bell\",\"isCorrect\":true},{\"answerText\":\"Steep\",\"isCorrect\":false},{\"answerText\":\"None of the above\",\"isCorrect\":false}]},{\"questionText\":\" ______ is the amount of equity required to cover unexpected losses based on a \\r\\n predetermined solvency standard.\",\"answerOptions\":[{\"answerText\":\"Stakeholder capital\",\"isCorrect\":false},{\"answerText\":\"Economic capital\",\"isCorrect\":true},{\"answerText\":\"Firm capital\",\"isCorrect\":false},{\"answerText\":\"None of the above\",\"isCorrect\":false}]},{\"questionText\":\" Any kind of risk analysis should start by taking a high-level objective and breaking it down \\r\\n into more tactical, operational key performance indicators (KPIs) and targets.\",\"answerOptions\":[{\"answerText\":\"True\",\"isCorrect\":true},{\"answerText\":\"False\",\"isCorrect\":false}]},{\"questionText\":\"There are ____ steps to integrate risk management into strategic planning.\",\"answerOptions\":[{\"answerText\":\"6\",\"isCorrect\":false},{\"answerText\":\"4\",\"isCorrect\":true},{\"answerText\":\"3\",\"isCorrect\":false},{\"answerText\":\"5\",\"isCorrect\":false}]},{\"questionText\":\"Strategic risks do not arise when a business strategy fails to deliver the expected outcomes, \\r\\n affecting the firm\\u2019s development and growth.\",\"answerOptions\":[{\"answerText\":\"True\",\"isCorrect\":true},{\"answerText\":\"False\",\"isCorrect\":false}]},{\"questionText\":\"Strategic and operational risk management is part of Enterprise Risk management (ERM)\",\"answerOptions\":[{\"answerText\":\"True\",\"isCorrect\":true},{\"answerText\":\"False\",\"isCorrect\":false}]},{\"questionText\":\"ERM also includes two other types of risk:\",\"answerOptions\":[{\"answerText\":\"Financial Risk management (FRM)\",\"isCorrect\":false},{\"answerText\":\"Compliance Risk management (CRM)\",\"isCorrect\":false},{\"answerText\":\"Both a and b\",\"isCorrect\":true},{\"answerText\":\"None of the above\",\"isCorrect\":false}]}]', NULL, NULL),
(64, 'Quiz', 66, 'TMC', '[{\"questionText\":\" Insider threats also increase because of the growing number of devices used by employees \\r\\n for their work-related activities.\",\"answerOptions\":[{\"answerText\":\"True\",\"isCorrect\":true},{\"answerText\":\"False\",\"isCorrect\":false}]},{\"questionText\":\"Cybercriminals carry out external threats.\",\"answerOptions\":[{\"answerText\":\"True\",\"isCorrect\":true},{\"answerText\":\"False\",\"isCorrect\":false}]},{\"questionText\":\"Market abuse and _____ are the related concepts by which individuals or companies use \\r\\n market sensitive inside information to manipulate the market.\",\"answerOptions\":[{\"answerText\":\" Money laundering\",\"isCorrect\":false},{\"answerText\":\"Malware\",\"isCorrect\":false},{\"answerText\":\"Insider dealing\",\"isCorrect\":true},{\"answerText\":\"None of the above\",\"isCorrect\":false}]},{\"questionText\":\"Any criminal activity involving the use of computers, as the illegal transfer of funds from one \\r\\n account to another or the stealing, changing, or erasing of data in an electronic data bank is?\",\"answerOptions\":[{\"answerText\":\"Electronic crime\",\"isCorrect\":true},{\"answerText\":\"Money laundering\",\"isCorrect\":false},{\"answerText\":\"Market abuse\",\"isCorrect\":false},{\"answerText\":\"None of the above\",\"isCorrect\":false}]},{\"questionText\":\"A scheme comes through spam emails or fake advertisements on websites.\",\"answerOptions\":[{\"answerText\":\"Hacking\",\"isCorrect\":false},{\"answerText\":\"Phishing\",\"isCorrect\":true},{\"answerText\":\"Market abuse\",\"isCorrect\":false},{\"answerText\":\"None of the above\",\"isCorrect\":false}]},{\"questionText\":\"Money laundering is the illegal process of making large amounts of money generated by \\r\\n criminal activity, such as drug trafficking or terrorist funding, appear to have come from a \\r\\n legitimate source.\",\"answerOptions\":[{\"answerText\":\"True\",\"isCorrect\":true},{\"answerText\":\"False\",\"isCorrect\":false}]},{\"questionText\":\"Customer due diligence (CDD) is not the act of performing background checks and other \\r\\n screening on the customer to ensure that they are properly risk-assessed before being \\r\\n onboarded.\",\"answerOptions\":[{\"answerText\":\"True\",\"isCorrect\":false},{\"answerText\":\"False\",\"isCorrect\":true}]},{\"questionText\":\"Records that are important or hard to replace should also be secured, Some other items that \\r\\n should be properly secured include:\",\"answerOptions\":[{\"answerText\":\"Passports\",\"isCorrect\":false},{\"answerText\":\"Military records\",\"isCorrect\":false},{\"answerText\":\"Birth and marriage certificates\",\"isCorrect\":false},{\"answerText\":\"All of the above\",\"isCorrect\":true}]},{\"questionText\":\"_____ risk is fundamental to the audit process because auditors cannot and do not attempt to check all transactions.\",\"answerOptions\":[{\"answerText\":\"Market\",\"isCorrect\":false},{\"answerText\":\"Audit\",\"isCorrect\":true},{\"answerText\":\"Financial\",\"isCorrect\":false},{\"answerText\":\"None of the above\",\"isCorrect\":false}]},{\"questionText\":\"A code of conduct is the most common policy within an organisation.\",\"answerOptions\":[{\"answerText\":\"True\",\"isCorrect\":true},{\"answerText\":\"False\",\"isCorrect\":false}]}]', NULL, NULL),
(65, 'Quiz', 48, 'TMC', '[{\"questionText\":\"Sustainable cash flow refers to a continuous stream of revenue.\",\"answerOptions\":[{\"answerText\":\"True\",\"isCorrect\":true},{\"answerText\":\"False\",\"isCorrect\":false}]},{\"questionText\":\"\\tIncreasing present cash flow helps your company acquire a continuous flow of money for expenses.\",\"answerOptions\":[{\"answerText\":\"True\",\"isCorrect\":true},{\"answerText\":\"False\",\"isCorrect\":false}]},{\"questionText\":\"A _____ describes the phases of access to credit by borrowers.\",\"answerOptions\":[{\"answerText\":\"Lending cycle\",\"isCorrect\":false},{\"answerText\":\"Credit cycle\",\"isCorrect\":true},{\"answerText\":\"Financing cycle\",\"isCorrect\":false},{\"answerText\":\"None of the above\",\"isCorrect\":false}]},{\"questionText\":\"Credit availability is not determined by risk and profitability to the lenders.\",\"answerOptions\":[{\"answerText\":\"True\",\"isCorrect\":false},{\"answerText\":\"False\",\"isCorrect\":true}]},{\"questionText\":\"\\t______ is one of the areas of investment management\",\"answerOptions\":[{\"answerText\":\"Credit Analysis\",\"isCorrect\":false},{\"answerText\":\"Risk Analysis\",\"isCorrect\":false},{\"answerText\":\"Portfolio Analysis\",\"isCorrect\":true},{\"answerText\":\"None of the above\",\"isCorrect\":false}]},{\"questionText\":\"The first sign that things are going wrong is a constant shortage of cash.\",\"answerOptions\":[{\"answerText\":\"True\",\"isCorrect\":true},{\"answerText\":\"False\",\"isCorrect\":false}]},{\"questionText\":\"Loans can be classified further into:\",\"answerOptions\":[{\"answerText\":\"secured and unsecured\",\"isCorrect\":false},{\"answerText\":\"open-end and closed-end\",\"isCorrect\":false},{\"answerText\":\"conventional types\",\"isCorrect\":false},{\"answerText\":\"All of the above\",\"isCorrect\":true}]},{\"questionText\":\"\\t_____ exercises may come in a variety of formats, and address any number of real-world issues and dilemmas.\